      <hedline>
        <hl1>Disability Assistance For the Homeless</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Center for Independence of the Disabled peer advocate Carl Herr letter on April 1 article about homeless man Patrick Garbiras and his difficulty in trying to receive disability assistance</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Patrick Garbiras, the homeless man profiled in ''Marking Time, Making Do'' (April 1), may be in a desperate situation, but he is not without hope. There are agencies that can assist him with his Social Security issues.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Patrick Garbiras, the homeless man profiled in ''Marking Time, Making Do'' (April 1), may be in a desperate situation, but he is not without hope. There are agencies that can assist him with his Social Security issues.</p>
        <p>Independent living centers, which exist in every borough, can provide representation for Social Security hearings free of charge and assist with a wide variety of disability-related issues, from coordinating with housing and vocational issues to all manner of benefits issues. I would strongly urge that Mr. Garbiras contact his local independent living center for these services.</p>
        <p>Carl Herr  Flushing, Queens</p>
        <p>The writer is a peer advocate, Center for Independence of the Disabled, New York-Queens.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
